https://mediabiasfactcheck.com/aptn-news.raw:
*Voting Polls do not affect MBFC bias ratings

These sources have minimal bias and use very few loaded words (wording that attempts to influence an audience by using appeal to emotion or stereotypes). The reporting is factual and usually sourced. These are the most credible media sources. See all Least Biased Sources.

Factual Reporting: HIGH
World Press Freedom Rank: Canada 22/180

Notes: Launched on September 1, 1999, Aboriginal Peoples Television Network (APTN) is a Canadian television national news program aired by the Aboriginal Peoples Television Network. They state their mission as "APTN is sharing our Peoples' journey, celebrating our cultures, inspiring our children and honoring the wisdom of our Elders." APTN offers a variety of programming related to Aboriginal peoples, including national news, documentaries, dramas, entertainment specials and more

APTN National News publishes news stories using The Canadian Press which is similar to the AP. Therefore, we rate APTN National News HIGH for factual reporting and a least biased news source. (M. Huitsing 9/16/15)

mediabiasfactcheck.com.name: Rare News
mediabiasfactcheck.com.raw:
*Voting Polls do not affect MBFC bias ratings

These media sources are slightly to moderately conservative in bias. They often publish factual information that utilizes loaded words (wording that attempts to influence an audience by using appeal to emotion or stereotypes) to favor conservative causes. These sources are generally trustworthy for information, but may require further investigation. See all Right-Center sources.

Factual Reporting: HIGH

Notes: Rare is an American website for viral news, original content and opinion, based in Washington, D.C. Rare has been compared to the websites Independent Journal Review, BuzzFeed, and The Huffington Post. The website has been described as libertarian-conservative, targeting a younger audience. (10/13/2016)

Notes: http://rare.us/
